##
# sitemaps - an easy way for wwebmasters to inform search engines about pages
# on their sites that are available for crawling.
# $Header$

= Document =
 * http://www.sitemaps.org/
 * http://www.sitemaps.org/protocol.html
 * http://www.sitemaps.org/faq.html
 * http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/09/sitemap.xsd
 * http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/09/siteindex.xsd
 * http://nchc.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/goog-sitemapgen/sitemap_gen-1.4.tar.gz

= Base rules =
 * With all XML files, any data values (including URLs) must use entity escape
   codes for: &, ', ", < and >.
 * Sitemap files must use UTF-8 encoding.
 * Use W3C Datetime encoding for the lastmod timestamps and all other dates
 * and times in this protocol.
	$ date --iso-8601=seconds -u -r /home/foo/www/bar.html
 * Sitemaps should be no larger than 10MB and can contain a maximum of 50, 000
   URLs. If not, use a Sitemap index file.
 * Use gzip to compress your Sitemaps.
 * Submit Sitemap using an HTTP request using wget, curl, or other:
	<searchengine_URL>/ping?sitemap=http://www.example.com/sitemap.gz
 *

